name: PlatformObject
summary:
An interface used to mark a [mapped](System.Mapped) platform type so that certain platform members can be implemented here. Useful when explicitly defining [Object] methods, such as toString(), which may have the same name as a member on platform Object. The explicitly defined methods can then call these methods.

These methods must not be implemented explicitly. The engine will automatically implement them when loading a type marked by this interface.
